{
  "message": "Remove DecodingText wrappers from all page hero headings\n\nReplaces <DecodingText text=\"...\" /> with plain static text in\nevery page-level hero heading across the site. The DecodingText\ncomponent still exists for use elsewhere, but wrapping page titles\nin it added a JavaScript animation dependency to every route's\ninitial paint for minimal visual payoff.\n\nPages affected (6 subpages):\n- architecture/page.tsx: \"Inside the\" / \"Machine.\"\n- beads/page.tsx: \"Project\" / \"Graph.\"\n- getting-started/page.tsx: \"Get\" / \"Started.\"\n- glossary/page.tsx: \"The\" / \"Glossary.\"\n- how-it-was-built/page.tsx: \"Built in\" / \"5 Days.\"\n- showcase/page.tsx: \"The\" / \"Showcase.\"\n\nHome page (app/page.tsx) required additional changes:\n- The <h1> becomes a <motion.h1> with its own fade-in/slide-up\n  animation (opacity 0\u21921, y 20\u21920, 0.8s duration with 0.2s delay\n  and custom cubic-bezier ease) to replace the staggered\n  DecodingText delays that previously animated each line\n- The FrankenGlitch wrapper around the red \"Monster\" text is\n  removed; the <span className=\"text-red-500\"> remains for color\n- Three separate DecodingText calls with staggered delays (0.2s,\n  0.6s, 1s) are replaced by a single motion.h1 entrance\n\nThe net effect is that hero headings now appear instantly (or with\na single coordinated fade on the home page) rather than scrambling\nin character-by-character, which was jarring on repeat visits and\nadded ~100ms of layout instability per heading.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
